<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbd080d6c-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c" identifier="/us/usc/t13/s184"><num value="184">§ 184.</num><heading> Definitions</heading>
<chapeau style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">For purposes of this subchapter—</chapeau><paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbd080d6d-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c" identifier="/us/usc/t13/s184/1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content> the term “local unit of general purpose government” means the government of a county, municipality, township, Indian tribe, Alaskan native village, or other unit of government (other than a State) which is a unit of general government, and</content>
</paragraph>
<paragraph style="-uslm-lc:I12" class="indent1" id="idbd080d6e-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c" identifier="/us/usc/t13/s184/2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content> the term “State” includes the District of Columbia.</content>
</paragraph>
<sourceCredit id="idbd080d6f-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/94/521/s8/a">Pub. L. 94–521, § 8(a)</ref>, <date date="1976-10-17">Oct. 17, 1976</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/90/2463">90 Stat. 2463</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbd080d70-76cd-11f0-842a-a3c49cc8bf0c">
